AN ACT relating to rail transit; directing the Legislative Commission to appoint a
Regional Rail Transit Advisory Working Group to conduct an interim
study relating to regional rail transit in [certain counties;] regional
communities; and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill directs the Legislative Commission to appoint a Regional Rail Transit Advisory
2 Working Group to conduct an interim study concerning the development of regional rail
3 transit in [Clark and Washoe Counties.] regional communities across the State. This bill
4 requires the Advisory Working Group to: (1) [for Clark and Washoe Counties,] study the
5 current state of regional rail transit and public transit, the need for regional rail transit, the
6 sources of money to support the development of regional rail transit and public and private
7 entities that should be involved in the development of regional rail transit; and (2) submit an
8 actionable plan for the development of regional rail transit in [Clark and Washoe Counties]
9 regional communities across the State and a written report of its findings and
10 recommendations to the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Growth and Infrastructure.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Legislative Commission shall appoint a Regional Rail
2 Transit Advisory Working Group to conduct a study during the 2025-2026 interim
3 concerning the development of regional rail transit in [Clark and Washoe Counties.]
4 regional communities across the State.
5 2. The Advisory Working Group must be composed of the following voting
6 members appointed by the Legislative Commission:
7 (a) One member who represents a labor union representing rail or public transit
8 employees in Clark County;

