18 (k) One member who is a resident of a county other than Clark County or
19 Washoe County, who has an interest or expertise in rail transit; and
20 (l) One member who represents a county other than Clark County or
21 Washoe County or a local government in such a county other than Clark
22 County or Washoe County or who is a representative of an organization
23 representing multiple such counties.
24 3. In addition to the members appointed pursuant to subsection 2, the
25 Legislative Commission may appoint any other nonvoting members to advise or
26 assist the Advisory Working Group.
27 4. During the 2025-2026 interim, the Advisory Working Group shall study:
28 (a) The current state of regional rail and public transit in [Clark and Washoe
29 Counties,] regional communities across the State, including, without limitation,
30 any current or future rail or public transit projects that are currently in the planning
31 stages or under development;
32 (b) The need for regional rail transit in [Clark and Washoe Counties;] regional
33 communities across the State;
34 (c) Potential sources of federal, state, private or nonprofit money to support the
35 development of regional rail transit in [Clark and Washoe Counties;] regional
36 communities across the State; and
37 (d) Any public or private entities which should be involved or oversee the
38 planning, development and implementation of regional rail transit in [Clark and
39 Washoe Counties.] regional communities across the State.
40 5. The Advisory Working Group shall, at its first meeting, elect a Chair and
41 Vice Chair from among its voting members.
42 6. The Advisory Working Group shall meet at the call of the Chair at least
43 once each month. A majority of the Advisory Working Group constitutes a quorum
44 for the transaction of business, and a majority of those voting members present at
45 any meeting is sufficient for any official action taken by the Advisory Working
46 Group.
47 7. The members of the Advisory Working Group serve without compensation
48 and are not entitled to the per diem and travel expenses provided for state officers
49 and employees generally.
50 8. On or before July 1, 2026, the Advisory Working Group shall prepare and
51 submit to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the Joint
52 Interim Standing Committee on Growth and Infrastructure:

